        <abstract> 
<p>Referring to a correspondent who had written about <hi rend="italic">Pelargonium</hi> plants whose leaves had become regularly edged with white, CD reports that nearly all the young leaves of box-trees he had planted have become symmetrically tipped with white. Though these facts seem trivial, CD believes the first appearance of any peculiarity which tends to become hereditary deserves being recorded.</p> 
        </abstract>
